<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed in Sluggish Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar was mixed Thursday in mild foreign  
exchange activity. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the euro was quoted at $1.0669, up  
from $1.0657 late Wednesday. The dollar also was quoted at 115.62 
Japanese yen, up from 115.35. 
</P>
<P>
	Sluggish currency markets took their lead from the lack of  
direction seen in the U.S. stock markets, which meandered for most 
of the day. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Gargano, manager of foreign exchange at First Union  
National Bank, Charlotte, N.C., said more activity in the euro is 
expected Friday after Germany reports its retail sales results for 
July. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.5012 Swiss francs, down from  
1.5029, and 1.4862 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4871. The British 
pound rose to $1.6119 from $1.6108. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
Based on Thursday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8332 German 
marks, down from 1.8349; and 6.1501 French francs, down from 
6.1538. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
