<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Priest Promoted Despite Affair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COVINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- A Roman Catholic priest was promoted to  
church pastor weeks after church officials learned he had fathered 
a child with a married woman. 
</P>
<P>
	The priest, the Rev. Joseph Gallenstein, has since received a  
three-month leave of absence at his own request. A statement issued 
by the Diocese of Covington said Gallenstein intends to remain a 
priest. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rev. Tom Sacksteder, a diocesan spokesman, said Gallenstein,  
who is in his early 40s, will work in the diocese when he returns 
but said he did not know where. 
</P>
<P>
	Sacksteder said the diocese had no comment on why it allowed  
Gallenstein to become pastor after it learned he had fathered a 
child. Catholic priests are required to be celibate. 
</P>
<P>
	``That is not a matter for the press. It is an internal matter  
for the church,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Diocesan officials learned in late March or early April that  
Gallenstein had fathered the child, the diocese said. It did not 
release any information about the child. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallenstein acknowledged his paternity and addressed the  
personal and spiritual issues involved, according to the diocese. 
</P>
<P>
	Gallenstein, whose leave of absence began July 26, was an  
associate pastor at St. Paul Church in Florence since June 1995 
before he was elevated to pastor last month. He was ordained in May 
1990. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
