<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Clash 2, Revolution 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Substitute Dario Brose's goal in the 77th  
minute lifted the San Jose Clash over the New England Revolution 
2-1 Thursday night in Major League Soccer. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was only the third in regulation time for San Jose  
(12-10). New England (8-13) dropped its fifth straight. 
</P>
<P>
	Brose, who came into the game eight minutes earlier, got through  
the New England defense and beat goalie Jeff Causey from 16 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	New England opened the scoring in the sixth minute when Ted  
Chronopoulos headed in a crossing pass from Ivan McKinley. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose tied it in the 54th minute, thanks to an own goal by  
Causey, playing for injured Walter Zenga. 
</P>
<P>
	The goal came when Jeff Baicher's corner kick was headed toward  
the right post by John Doyle. Causey made an awkward save and 
accidentally kicked the ball into his net. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
