<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 06:40:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 3; Nasdaq Gains 2 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down three  
points in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 7-6 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up two points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up a fraction. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors seems to be paying little attention to July's  
stronger-than-expected report on retail sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Such a strong number might normally scare a market that already  
is uneasy about an overheating economy. 
</P>
<P>
	But analysts say much of the increase came in the volatile  
automotive sector, and isn't indicative of a broad trend. 
</P>
<P>
	At the same time, market-watchers say yesterday's strong gains  
on Wall Street are the reaction to an oversold condition in the 
market. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices are modestly lower. Overseas stock market averages  
remain sharply higher. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
