	NEW YORK (AP) -- Edgardo Alfonzo homered and tied a career high  
with five RBIs Wednesday night as the New York Mets beat the San 
Diego Padres 12-5. Alfonzo, who went 2-for-4, hit a two-run double 
off Sterling Hitchcock in a four-run fifth as the Mets overcame a 
5-2 deficit. Mike Piazza broke out of an 0-for-9 slump with an RBI 
single that scored Alfonzo to tie it at 5. Piazza went 3-for-4 with 
three RBIs. 


</P>
