<HEADLINE> Denny Lambert Loses Arbitration Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Nashville Predators have won their  
arbitration case against left wing Denny Lambert. 
</P>
<P>
	An arbitrator in Toronto sided with the team Wednesday and  
Lambert was given a one-year contract worth $465,000. He was 
seeking about $700,000 after earning $245,000 last season. 
</P>
<P>
	``He still got a significant increase,'' Predators general  
manager David Poile said. ``He's a pro. I hope he's happy and that 
he can put the arbitration process behind him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lambert, 29, played every position but goalie for Nashville last  
season, totaling five goals, 11 assists and 218 penalty minutes in 
76 games. 
  	   	
