<HEADLINE> Brochu Sets Deadline for Expo Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTREAL (AP) -- Montreal Expos president Claude Brochu set Sept.  
30 as the deadline for the team's partners to buy his 7.2 percent 
share of the team, which is worth about $10 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Brochu has been the team's president since Sept. 6, 1986, and  
became managing partner when Charles Bronfman sold the club to a 
group headed by Brochu in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
	Expos chairman Jacques Menard has taken the lead role in recent  
months in putting together a new ownership group that would 
purchase the franchise and obtain financing for a new ballpark. 
</P>
<P>
	New York art dealer Jeffrey Loria is expected to pay about $50  
million and becoming the new managing partner. Any sale must be 
approved by three-quarters of NL owners and a majority of AL 
owners. 
