<DOCNO> APW19990812.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 14:20:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fassel To Miss Giants Preseason Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	New York Giants coach Jim Fassel left the team in Albany, N.Y.,  
on Thursday, one day before the preseason opener, to be with his 
critically ill mother in Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
	Fassel had intended to coach the game against the Minnesota  
Vikings and then travel to Arizona on Saturday to be with his 
mother, Dorothy, but her condition worsened, Giants spokesman Pat 
Hanlon said. 
</P>
<P>
	Dorothy Fassel has been ill for some time with a kidney-related  
illness, Hanlon said. She collapsed in a hospital in the Phoenix 
area on Tuesday and she has been on a ventilator. 
</P>
<P>
	``Her condition has gotten more serious and Jim decided to go to  
Phoenix to be with her,'' Hanlon said. 
</P>
<P>
	Fassel notified the team of his plans right before it left  
training camp at the University at Albany to take the flight to 
Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	Offensive coordinator Jim Skipper and defensive coordinator John  
Fox will run the team on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	It is not known when Fassel will rejoin the Giants, Hanlon said.  
</P>
<P>
	The Giants also announced Thursday they had been awarded running  
back Reynard Rutherford on waivers from Oakland. The former 
California running back has spent parts of the last three seasons 
on the practice squads of the San Francisco 49ers and the Raiders. 
He has not played a down in a regular season game. 
</P>
<P>
	The Giants have been short of running backs with Gary Brown,  
LeShon Johnson, Joe Montgomery and Raymond Priester sidelined with 
minor injuries. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
