<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Low pressure produced rain in the Midwest and Plains on  
Thursday, with hot, hazy conditions along the East Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	Rain and storms struck parts of Iowa, Illinois, Wisconsin, and  
Indiana, along with portions of Minnesota, North Dakota and 
Montana. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair skies and sticky heat continued in Kansas, Oklahoma and  
Texas, and along the East Coast. Afternoon temperatures reached 
into the 100s. 
</P>
<P>
	Scattered showers and thunderstorms drenched southern Florida  
and other spots in the mid-Atlantic region and the Gulf Coast. Fair 
and dry weather also stretched west across the lower Mississippi 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
	Mild conditions prevailed in most regions of the West.  
</P>
<P>
	The cleanup continued in Salt Lake City after a rare tornado  
tore through downtown. One person was killed and dozens were 
injured in Wednesday's twister. 
</P>
<P>
	Thursday, the afternoon high in the lower 48 states was 100  
degrees in Little Rock, Ark. The low was 37 degrees in Flagstaff, 
Ariz. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
