<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 12:40:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mondale Preps Ventura for Trade Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- It was more than a typical meeting  
between two politicians from Minnesota when Walter Mondale, former 
vice president and ambassador to Japan, helped Gov. Jesse Ventura 
prepare for an upcoming trade mission. 
</P>
<P>
	The Minnesota governor requested the meeting Wednesday with  
Mondale, who said he won't join Ventura on the November trip to 
Japan. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't like to be upstaged,'' Mondale quipped.  
</P>
<P>
	The governor spent about half an hour in his office with  
Mondale, who left his post as ambassador to Japan two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	``He has the experience so I listen to him,'' Ventura said of  
Mondale. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura used to wrestle professionally in Japan and is well  
known there. Mondale said the governor's stature in Japan will 
create possibilities that wouldn't be open to all governors. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
