<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990812.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-12 08:30:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bayer Second Quarter Profits Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEVERKUSEN, Germany (AP) -- A difficult second quarter hurt Bayer  
AG's first-half profit margins, but the German pharmaceutical maker 
said Thursday its full-year operating profit should be close to 
last year's levels. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales in the first half of 1999 slipped 2 percent to $15.2  
billion, falling short of analysts' forecasts. 
</P>
<P>
	First-half operating profit fell 3.7 percent to $1.6 billion,  
excluding $1 billion in proceeds from the stock market flotation of 
a 65 percent stake in its Belgian photo-imaging group Agfa-Gevaert 
NV. 
</P>
<P>
	Bayer said a second-half economic upturn for the industry will  
help it implement much-needed price increases, especially in 
chemicals. It said it expects operating profit to come close to 
last year's levels of $3.4 billion, and said the gain from Agfa 
will push net income well ahead of last year's $1.7 billion. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
