<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Falls in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MADRID, Spain (AP) -- Spain's unemployment rate fell to 15.6  
percent in the second quarter of 1999, from 17 percent in the first 
quarter, the National Statistics Institute said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The number of unemployed, including first-time job seekers, fell  
to 2.55 million in the second quarter from a 2.76 million in the 
first quarter, the Institute said. 
</P>
<P>
	The INE's quarterly unemployment data is based on the results a  
survey of around 64,000 families throughout Spain. It is watched 
more closely than the Spanish Labor Ministry's monthly 
jobless-claims figure as it includes information on everyone out of 
work, rather just than those eligible for benefits. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite the downward trend, unemployment in Spain remains far  
higher than the European Union average of 9.4 percent for June. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
