	Ill. GOP Leaders Flock to Bush  
</P>
<P>
	SPRINGFIELD, Ill. (AP) -- Republican leaders in Illinois flocked  
to the side of GOP presidential candidate George W. Bush today as 
he made several campaign stops en route to Iowa. Dozens of state 
officials endorsed Bush, the governor of Texas, during a statehouse 
rally. Gov. George Ryan put his powerful campaign apparatus in 
Bush's corner. ``Without question, he is the best candidate 
available,'' Ryan said. Former Govs. James R. Thompson and Jim 
Edgar gave their support, too -- along with the attorney general, 
lieutenant governor, state treasurer and a flock of legislators. 

</P>
