	Congo Vaccinations Create Cease-Fire  
</P>
<P>
	KISANGANI, Congo (AP) -- Congolese rebels declared a unilateral,  
weeklong cease-fire in fighting against government troops today to 
allow polio vaccinations for an estimated 10 million children. 
Congo's first national campaign to vaccinate against the crippling 
disease is sponsored by the United Nations and starts tomorrow. 
U.N. agencies have distributed vaccination kits to local health 
centers, where mothers have been urged by local leaders and aid 
workers to bring their children under the age of five for their 
first polio shots. 

</P>
