<HEADLINE> Elkington Withdraws From PGA Tourney  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEDINAH, Ill. (AP) -- Steve Elkington, the 1995 PGA Champion,  
withdrew from the tournament this afternoon after his caddie 
complained of heart problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Rather than get another caddie to carry his bag, Elkington  
withdrew shortly before he was supposed to tee off and went to the 
hospital to be with his caddie, Joe Grillo. Grillo was in stable 
condition at Glen Oaks Hospital in Glendale Heights, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
	Elkington was replaced by Bob Friend.  
</P>
<P>
	This is the second straight PGA Tour event in Chicago in which a  
caddie has had heart problems. 
</P>
<P>
	At the Western Open last month, caddie Garland Dempsey's heart  
stopped and he collapsed while walking off the 15th tee during the 
third rond. Paramedics had to use a defibrillator to restart his 
heart. 
</P>
