<HEADLINE> Dollar Rises, Japan Stocks Higher / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar continued its rise against the yen late  
today following overnight gains on Wall Street. Japanese stocks 
closed higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 115.68 yen at late-afternoon, up 0.98 yen from  
late Wednesday in Tokyo and also above its late New York level of 
115.35 yen overnight. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 211.81 points,  
or 1.23 percent, to 17,422.97 at the end of the day's trading. On 
Wednesday, the average closed up 9.07 points, or 0.05 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency trading, Japanese banks bought dollars after seeing  
the gains in the U.S. stock and bond markets overnight, a dealer at 
a European bank said. 
</P>
<P>
	But overall, movement was meager, as the dollar was caught  
between offers from some U.S. investors and Japanese exporters and 
bids from Japanese investors. Near the end of the session, the 
dollar moved in a range of 115.33 yen to 115.77 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	While the dollar is still firm, ongoing concern the U.S. Federal  
Reserve will raise interest rates is keeping market players from 
aggressively buying dollars. Some investors worry that higher 
borrowing costs would slow the U.S. economy. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro traded at 123.36 yen at  
late-afternoon, up from 122.99 late Wednesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, prices opened higher today as investor  
sentiment was bolstered by overnight rises in New York and Chicago, 
where futures prices advanced. 
</P>
<P>
	``Shares have been boosted by the overnight rise in New York and  
the yen's relative stability around the mid-115 yen level,'' said 
Hidenori Karaki, general manager at Tokyo-Mitsubishi Personal 
Securities. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 132.65 points  
to 10,787.80 at Wednesday's close. The technology-laden Nasdaq 
Composite Index climbed 74.87 to 2,564.98. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section closed up 17.80 points, or 1.25 percent, to 1,438.44. 
The TOPIX closed down 3.61 points, or 0.25 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 214 10-year Japanese government  
bond fell to 1.8250 percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.8400 
percent, driving its price up to 99.78 yen from 99.65 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
