<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Columbine Victim Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) -- Keeping with her wish for a private  
recovery, Columbine High School shooting victim Anne Marie 
Hochhalter was released quietly from the hospital on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Although she chose not to have a news conference, Miss  
Hochhalter, 17, thanked her family, friends and Craig Hospital 
staff in a written statement. 
</P>
<P>
	``I still have many obstacles to overcome, but I know that I can  
do it, and God will give me strength along the way,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Hochhalter took a direct hit in her spinal cord, paralyzing  
her from the waist down, in the April 20 rampage. She plans to 
return to Columbine for her senior year. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Castaldo, 17, who was also paralyzed in the shootings,  
is now the only Columbine victim still in the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Thirteen people were killed and 23 others injured when seniors  
Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold opened fire in the school, then took 
their own lives. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
