<HEADLINE> Redskins' Ken Harvey Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ASHBURN, Va. (AP) -- Linebacker Ken Harvey, a four-time Pro  
Bowler, retired today from the Washington Redskins. 
</P>
<P>
	Harvey, who played 11 seasons with the Cardinals and Redskins,  
injured a knee early last season. He was released by the Redskins 
and re-signed, but missed the first week-and-a-half of training 
camp while continuing rehabilitation on the knee. 
</P>
<P>
	He was a first-round draft pick, 12th overall, of the Cardinals  
in 1988 and signed as a free agent with the Redskins in 1994. He 
made the Pro Bowl four straight years in Washington, from 1994 to 
1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Harvey's best season was in 1994 when he registered 13 1/2 sacks.  
  	   	
