<HEADLINE> Telefonica, IDT Ally for U.S. Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- IDT Corp. and Telefonica S.A. of Spain  
have formed a joint partnership to sell Internet and telephone 
services to the Hispanic market in the United States, the companies 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
	The broad-based venture between the two telecommunication  
companies will offer Internet access, prepaid calling cards and 
other phone services, David Brainson, vice president of finance for 
IDT, said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Madrid-based Telefonica, the leading telecom provider in Spain  
and Portugal, has half of its 55 million customers in Latin 
America. Telefonica is trying to expand its presence to Latinos in 
the United States and elsewhere by using IDT technology and know 
how, IDT spokesman Larry Weisman said. 
</P>
<P>
	IDT is attempting to increase its presence among the 30 million  
Hispanics in the United States by using Telefonica's name 
recognition and networking services. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this year, IDT began marketing an Internet access  
service aimed at Hispanic users called Nuestra Voz, or Our Voice. 
Telefonica has a Web portal service called Ole! IDT, however, did 
not say how the two services would be connected, if at all. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
