<HEADLINE> Ohio Cop Has Impeccable Timing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- A police officer who was instructing bank  
employees on what to do when a robbery occurs had to interrupt his 
teaching when a man robbed a teller in front of him. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm talking with the assistant manager when a teller said, `Go  
get him, he just robbed us,''' said Officer Duane A. Ward. 
</P>
<P>
	When the suspect entered the Bank One office on Wednesday, he  
apparently didn't notice Ward in uniform, authorities said. The 
suspect gave a note to a teller and took an undisclosed amount of 
cash. 
</P>
<P>
	Ward, 30, tackled the man in a motel parking lot 50 yards from  
the bank. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was just wanting to catch him. I didn't know who he was,''  
said Ward. ``Money was flying out of his bag like it was a 
Christmas giveaway.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The suspect was identified as Ricky Lynn Caudill, 43. Police  
have charged Caudill, a homeless man, with one count of robbery for 
the bank holdup and one count of aggravated robbery for trying to 
take the officer's gun. 
</P>
<P>
	The FBI has linked Caudill to 13 other bank robberies.  




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
