has won her last two starts and five of six. 
</P>
<P>
	Enjoy Lavec, third in last weekend's $1 million Hambletonian,  
heads the first Zweig split, carrying a $109,075 purse. The son of 
Pine Chip has made in excess of $180,000 in 1999, winning twice. 
</P>
<P>
	Luc Ouellette drives from post No. 3 for trainer Jimmy Takter.  
</P>
<P>
	CR Commando, last season's 2-year-old champ, starts right  
outside Enjoy Lavec in post No. 4 with trainer/driver Carl Allen. 
</P>
<P>
	Sunday's closing-day Syracuse program also features the $52,000  
Zweig Filly Trot as well as the $64,350 New York Sire Stakes for 
3-year-old pacing colts and geldings. 
  	   	
