<HEADLINE> Seahawks Sign Top Draft Choice King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- The Seattle Seahawks signed first-round  
draft choice Lamar King and unrestricted free agent wide receiver 
Michael Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
	King, a 6-foot-3, 294-pound defensive lineman from Saginaw  
(Mich.) Valley State, was the 22nd player selected in April's 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-4, 195-pound Jackson has played in the NFL for eight  
seasons -- five with the Cleveland Browns and three with the 
Baltimore Ravens. He had 38 receptions for 477 yards and no 
touchdowns with the Ravens last season. 
</P>
