<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CompUSA Delays Earnings Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Computer retailer CompUSA Inc. said Thursday it  
will delay releasing fourth-quarter financial results by nearly two 
weeks while it completes work on a restructuring move. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said the delay, from Aug. 18 until after financial  
markets close Aug. 30, will allow it to discuss the restructuring 
changes at the same time it releases earnings for the quarter ended 
June 26. 
</P>
<P>
	The decision to delay its earnings report does not relate to its  
results of operations and is not an indication of a change in its 
previous statements regarding the quarter, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts surveyed by First Call estimate the company will post  
fourth quarter losses of 24 cents a share, compared with a loss of 
19 cents a share in the year-ago quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	CompUSA operates 208 stores in 82 U.S. metropolitan areas. In  
late June, the company said it was working on a long list of 
strategic moves to redefine its business concept. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said in June it will cut 1,000 to 1,500 jobs, or  
about 7 percent of its work force of 21,000 and plans to shift its 
focus from personal computer sales to consumer electronics. The 
shift to consumer electronics is in response to the decline in PC 
prices. 
</P>
<P>
	Some changes, such as the closing of four stores and a  
distribution center, have been announced. The company needs more 
time to finish work on the others before discussing them when it 
releases financial results, said spokeswoman Suzanne Shelton. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't predict how people are going to react'' to the delay,  
Ms. Shelton said. ``It's not related to the financial reporting.'' 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
