Milhouse in Anaheim and showed trouble with the lateral collateral 
ligament. 
</P>
<P>
	The Angels, idle Thursday, open a seven-game road trip Friday  
night in Detroit having lost six straight games and 22 of their 
last 26. 
</P>
<P>
	Erstad, 25, has played in all but two of his team's 113 games  
and is hitting .246 with 10 homers and 37 RBIs. He hit .296 with 19 
homers and 82 RBIs last season. 
  	   	
