<HEADLINE> Former Dolphin Clayton Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Former Miami Dolphins wide receiver  
Mark Clayton was arrested for failing to pay over $12,000 in child 
support and for driving with a suspended license. 
</P>
<P>
	Clayton, who played with the Dolphins from 1983 through 1992,  
was arrested Wednesday while conducting personal business at the 
South Satellite Broward County Courthouse, according to a release 
issued by the Broward County Sheriff's Office. 
</P>
<P>
	Clayton was taken to the county jail after Broward's Support  
Enforcement Division records showed he owed $12,441.25 in unpaid 
child support. 
</P>
<P>
	He was released from jail Thursday after paying $6,639.75 in  
back support payments and posting a $500 bond. 
</P>
<P>
	``If the remaining child support is not paid, Clayton will be  
notified by mail, his license may be suspended, and a warrant may 
be issued for his arrest,'' according to the sheriff's office 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The 38-year-old retired NFL star lives in suburban Pembroke  
Pines. 
</P>
<P>
	He was the Dolphins' leading receiver in 1984, 1988, 1989 and  
1991 and still holds the team record for receiving yards in a 
season (1,389 in 1984) and most receptions (86 in 1988). 
</P>
<P>
	Clayton also holds Dolphins career records for receptions (550)  
and touchdowns (81). 
  	   	
</P>
