<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Playoff Ticket Prices Up 40 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- While World Series ticket prices will remain the  
same this year after doubling last season, fans will pay as much as 
40 percent more to attend the league championships. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland became the first team to announce its postseason  
ticket prices, saying Thursday the top price of a ticket for the 
league championship series will be $85. 
</P>
<P>
	That's a 42 percent increase from last year's top of $60 and 70  
percent above the $50 charged for the best seats in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland is charging up to $50 for the first round division  
series, an increase of 35 percent from $37 last year. 
</P>
<P>
	For the World Series, box seats will remain at $150 and $120,  
with reserved seats at $100 and $85, bleachers and general 
admission at $40 and standing room at $25. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition, teams charge higher for premium seats. The New York  
Yankees charged $700 a seat for the front-row Legends Boxes last 
year and $300 for their box seats with waiter service. The Yankees' 
postseason ticket plan for this year has not been finalized. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1996, most Series box seats cost $75, while reserved seats  
were $50 and general admission $30. 
</P>
<P>
	The commissioner's office told teams its league championship  
ticket prices should range from $40 to $75 this year. Last year, 
the commissioner's office set specific prices, saying box seats 
should sell for $60, reserved seats for $45 and general admission 
and bleachers for $30. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland's top price is higher because Jacobs Field has many  
high- and low-priced seats with relatively few in the middle range. 
The Indians are charging $70 for lesser box seats for the league 
championship, while reserved seats will cost $45 and $35, with 
standing room and general admission at $25. 
</P>
<P>
	For the division series, the commissioner's office gave teams a  
range of $17 to $35, a slight change from last year's range of 
$17.50 to $30. Cleveland is selling tickets for $50, $40, $35, $25, 
$20 and $15. 
</P>
<P>
	Super Bowl tickets cost $400 (luxury suites) and $325 last year,  
a $50 hike. Ticket prices for January's game in Atlanta have not 
been set, NFL spokesman Greg Aiello said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	In the NBA and NHL, teams set their own postseason ticket  
prices. The top tickets for the NBA Finals this year cost $2,700 
per game in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	For the Stanley Cup finals, Dallas had a top price of $350 and  
Buffalo had a high of $111. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
