<HEADLINE> Clark Charged in Minor League Brawl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	O'FALLON, Mo. (AP) -- Former major league star Jack Clark was  
charged with assaulting a police officer following a bench-clearing 
brawl during a minor league game that resulted in 14 suspensions. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark, manager of the River City Rascals of the Class A Frontier  
League, turned himself in to O'Fallon police Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Malcolm Fichman, manager of the Johnstown (Pa.) Johnnies, was  
charged with failing to obey a police officer. He was arrested 
following Tuesday night's brawl after he refused to leave the 
field. 
</P>
<P>
	Both were released after posting $300 bond.  
</P>
<P>
	Police were called to Ozzie Smith Sports Complex in suburban St.  
Louis after the brawl began. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Fallon Police Chief Steve Talbott said the 20-minute fight  
started after Johnnies batter Justin Headley was struck in the back 
by a pitch from Randy Eversgerd in the top of the the eighth. 
Rascals batters Jim Schmidt, Aaron Jawawroski and Dan Graham had 
been hit earlier by Landon Hessler. 
</P>
<P>
	Rascals general manager Pat Daly said there was a lot of tension  
in the game because the two teams are fighting for a playoff spot. 
</P>
<P>
	Umpires called the game after the fights, giving the Rascals a  
9-4 victory and putting them two games ahead of the Johnnies. 
</P>
<P>
	No serious injuries were reported to police. No other charges  
were expected, Talbott said. 
</P>
<P>
	The teams played again Wednesday night in O'Fallon. But they  
were without Clark and Fichman, who were suspended by the league, 
along with six members of each team. The terms of their suspensions 
varied but were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark, who played for the St. Louis Cardinals from 1985-87, said  
Wednesday he had apologized to police. He said there were so many 
people on the field that he didn't realize he was swinging at an 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
	Eversgerd was suspended, as was Graham, his team's catcher. Also  
suspended from the Rascals were infielder Dustin Rogelstad, 
outfielder Kevin Pitts, shortstop Jason Rakers and catcher Bill 
Black. 
</P>
<P>
	Hessler was suspended along with three of his teammates and two  
of his coaches: pitcher Brian Jollise, designated hitter Gabe 
Memmert, center fielder Mike Pilger, batting coach Tom Tornincasa 
and pitching coach Tom Donovan. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
