<HEADLINE> General Mills Buys Gardetto's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GOLDEN VALLEY, Minn. (AP) -- General Mills Inc. said Thursday it  
has purchased Milwaukee-based Gardetto's Bakery Inc., a 
family-owned company that makes and sells baked snack mixes and 
flavored pretzels nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
	General Mills, which did not disclose the terms of the deal,  
will now have a stronger presence in vending machines, convenience 
stores and other non-grocery outlets. 
</P>
<P>
	``We plan to build the Gardetto's brand with innovative  
marketing, expanded distribution and development of new snack 
varieties,'' Steve Sanger, General Mills chairman and chief 
executive, said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	General Mills will continue production at the Gardetto's plant  
in Milwaukee, and expects to retain most of the company's 235 
employees. Gardetto's Bakery had $100 million in sales last year. 
</P>
<P>
	John Gardetto, 64, president of the snack company his father  
founded in 1932, plans to retire. 


  	   	
</P>
