<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Arbiter Gives Rolston $2.7 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- New Jersey Devils left-winger Brian Rolston was  
awarded a two-year deal worth $2.7 million by an NHL arbitrator. 
</P>
<P>
	Rolston had been seeking a $1.7-million over one year and the  
Devils were offering $975,000, according to his agent, Stephen 
Bartlett. 
</P>
<P>
	NHL teams are allowed to dictate the length of the contract and  
the Devils set Rolston's at two years. The arbitrator's decision 
Wednesday gave Rolston $1.3 million in the first year and $1.473 
million in the second. 
</P>
<P>
	The 26-year-old from Flint, Mich., had 24 goals and 33 assists  
in 82 games and one goal in seven playoff games last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
